?thread=19692117#t19692117","above":19690837,"upictitle":"George R.R. Martin: Spain","article":"I am familiar with his work, but don't believe I have ever met him personally.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"November 2 2014, 22:34:08 UTC","parent":19690837,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Do you know RAW?","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"grrm","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"grrm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"grrm","ctime_ts":1414967648,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19695957#t19695957","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19695957#t19695957","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19695957#t19695957","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_2853479","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://plus.google.com/113787774813398657068","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19695957,"talkid":76937,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19695957#t19695957","upictitle":"Sam Brody: pic#0","article":"I am loving WOIAF so far. Finished the first half and am up to the Seven Kingdoms part.<br /><br />I especially enjoy the maester's \"historian\" voice, and his efforts to be a good scholar.<br /><br />One thing that has me wondering, actually, and this may be one of the weirdest world-building queries you've had yet -- has to do with the genres of writing the maesters of the Citadel produce. There's clearly history of figures and places, political history, as well as geographical and zoological treatises. But what I'd really be interested in knowing is if there is some equivalent to philosophy -- something that isn't empirical science, and isn't just reporting on types of magic, but is a type of speculation about what the world is made of and how it works, etc. Esoteric, I know, but I imagine there must be some maesters toiling away on arguments like \"the whole world is made of water,\" or perhaps on some other types of arguments reconciling rationality with the ideas acceptable to the Faith...","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"November 3 2014, 01:33:35 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"WOIAF","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://plus.google.com/113787774813398657068","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/google-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Sam Brody","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_2853479","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=72827090&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Sam Brody","ctime_ts":1414978415,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/51443191/3030116","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19700565#t19700565","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19700565#t19700565","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19700565#t19700565","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"hippoiathanatoi","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19700565,"talkid":76955,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19700565#t19700565","above":19695957,"upictitle":"Elio &amp; Linda: Elio","article":"Good question!<br /><br />I would hazard that Barth's works -- referenced (and dismissed) quite often in the book -- probably touched on the philosophical quite a bit. He was a man of many talents.<br />","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"November 3 2014, 19:34:01 UTC","parent":19695957,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: WOIAF","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"hippoiathanatoi","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"hippoiathanatoi","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"hippoiathanatoi","ctime_ts":1415043241,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/123131595/69960746","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19709781#t19709781","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19709781#t19709781","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19709781#t19709781","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_2525024","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://www.facebook.com/eugene.toussaint","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19709781,"talkid":76991,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19709781#t19709781","upictitle":"Eugene Toussaint: pic#123131595","article":"Take my money now, I would so buy a 900 page version of the world of ice and fire. I am up to Daeron II in this one.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"November 6 2014, 01:19:25 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"World ","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://www.facebook.com/eugene.toussaint","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Eugene Toussaint","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_2525024","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=69960746&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Eugene Toussaint","ctime_ts":1415236765,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/95070601/23089682","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19711829#t19711829","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19711829#t19711829","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19711829#t19711829","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"purplemoon3","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://purplemoon3.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19711829,"talkid":76999,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/387157.html?thread=19711829#t19711829","upictitle":"purplemoon3: Supernatural","article":"Dear Mr. Martin,<br />I started with the TV show, and have since spent many an hour at work listening to the Audiobooks for A Song of Ice and Fire.  Recently I was struck by a thought continues to nag at me: how did the Starks deal with fleas? My first thought was that the North would be too cold for ticks and fleas, but my second thought was that maybe the just have extra hardy pests up North.  Did Maester Luwin know natural flea remedies?  Was Sansa upset that they had to dip into the lemon stash to mix up a flea deterrent?  This is probably a silly question and if you've answered it before I apologize, but I truly love the world you've created and this tiny aspect has been bothering me like a bowling ball under a mattress.<br />Sincerely,<br />PM3<br />","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"November 7 2014, 03:07:28 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Direwolf Question","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://purplemoon3.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"purplemoon3","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"purplemoon3","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://purplemoon3.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"purplemoon3","ctime_ts":1415329648,"tracked":0}]}